This paper is most likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with intrusion detection, which is a key aspect of network security. It could also belong to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with network traffic data. Additionally, the paper suggests the use of machine learning techniques to infer mature functions, which could place it in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a multi-dimensional approach towards intrusion detection, which could also place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
